headline.main: DARDANELLES SHUT; Mining of Key Sea Link Hinted in Naval Curb on Ship Transit WAR VESSELS HEAD WEST Diplomats Busy in Ankara -- Soviet Aid Held Possible for Turks and British DARDANELLES SHUT BY TURKISH ORDER STRATEGIC STRAITS OF DARDANELLES CLOSED BY TURKS TO UNAUTHORIZED SHIPPING

lead_paragraph: ISTANBUL, Turkey, March 2 -- The Turkish Navy Ministry announced tonight that the strategic Dardanelles had been closed to all ships except those having special permits and employing Turkish naval pilots. The ruling went into effect tonight.
abstract: USSR aid to Brit and Turks held possible
